%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdonald-trump-hush-money-trial-hope-hicks-witness-stand-2024-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eformer%20White%20House%20communications%20director%20Hope%20Hicks%20testify%3C%2Fa%3E%20about%20a%202018%20Oval%20Office%20conversation%2C%20in%20which%20she%20said%20Trump%20told%20her%20he%20was%20relieved%20the%20hush-money%20story%20broke%20%3Cem%3Eafter%3C%2Fem%3E%20the%20election%2C%20rather%20than%20before.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20testimony%20was%20%26quot%3Bdevastating%26quot%3B%20and%20showed%20Trump%20considered%20the%20hush-money%20payment%20to%20be%20vital%20to%20his%20campaign%2C%20prosecutor%20Joshua%20Steinglass%20told%20the%20jury%20in%20closing%20statements.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFlorence%20thought%20this%20conversation%20might%20arguably%20be%20official%20under%20the%20SCOTUS%20opinion%20%26quot%3Bbecause%20she%20worked%20for%20the%20administration.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20opinion%20says%20that%20in%20the%20DC%20insurrection%20case%2C%20Trump's%20discussions%20with%20his%20acting%20attorney%20general%20%26quot%3Bare%20readily%20categorized%20in%20light%20of%20the%20nature%20of%20the%20President's%20official%20relationship%20to%20the%20office%20held%20by%20that%20individual%26quot%3B%20and%20are%20therefore%20immune%20from%20prosecution%20and%20cannot%20be%20used%20against%20him.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BBut%20even%20then%2C%20he's%20talking%20with%20Hicks%20about%20something%20relating%20to%20his%20personal%20life%2C%26quot%3B%20Florence%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEither%20way%20%E2%80%94%20whether%20it%20was%20properly%20or%20improperly%20shared%20with%20the%20jury%20%E2%80%94%20the%20Hicks%20conversation%20is%20more%20corroborative%20than%20substantive%2C%20and%20the%20verdict%20would%20survive%20without%20it%2C%20Florence%20and%20Moscow%20agreed.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%22836%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Excerpt%20from%20a%20footnote%20in%20a%20financial%20disclosure%20form%20D